result.execSummary:
The defendant Patrick J Dickman was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of synthetic cannabinoid - 2nd+ offense, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(em).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Case called @ 1:06 p.m. Defendant Patrick J Dickman in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Defendant Patrick J Dickman in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. The court entertains waiver of the preliminary hearing. The court accepts voluntary waiver of the preliminary hearing. Defendant bound over for trial. Information filed by ADA Anderson. Receipt admitted - Reading waived. Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Cts 1 & 5 - NC. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Cts 2-4 - DRI. No statement by DE. Court orders: Ct 1 -  42 days WCJ - 32 days CFTS - Time served sentence, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA sample to be provided. Ct 2 - 90 days WCJ - Huber, GT, No CFTS - I/S - 1 year probation - Conditions: AODA and follow through, any other terms or conditions as deemed appropriate by supervising agent, costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. Appeal rights given.

Case called @ 1:13 p.m. Defendant Patrick J Dickman in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi. Scott C. Blader  appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Motion by Atty Szilagyi for bond modification - requesting a signature bond. Statement by DA Blader regarding bond - DE has two pending matters in other jurisdictions. Defendant has had missed court appearances in the past. Statement by the defendant. The court declines to modify the bond in any way based on the history of missed court appearances by the defendant and alleged bond violations.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 28, 2015 at 01:00 pm.
